item.description:
arXiv:2604.25442v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: We establish new quantitative estimates for general systems of functions with wavelet-type dyadic structure. These estimates are applied to obtain the optimal growth of various types of Weyl multipliers for certain wavelet-type systems. Some of our results are sufficiently general to allow the orthogonality assumption to be removed. In particular, as a consequence of these estimates we show that the condition
  \begin{equation*}
  \sum_{n=1}^\infty\frac{1}{nw(n)}<\infty
  \end{equation*}
  is necessary and sufficient for an increasing sequence $w(n)$ to be an almost everywhere unconditional convergence Weyl multiplier for an arbitrary wavelet-type system. We also prove that $\log n$ is an almost everywhere convergence Weyl multiplier for any rearranged wavelet-type system, and that this bound is optimal.
